      "text": "in the treatise on insolubles in his Logica Magna, Paul develops and endorses Swyneshed's solution, which stood out against this 'multiplemeanings' approach in offering a solution that took insolubles at face value, meaning no more than is explicit in what they say",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "A3": {
      "text": "On this account, insolubles imply their own falsity, and that is why, in so falsifying themselves, they are false",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "A4": {
      "text": "Notice that not everything I have said here, or in other treatises, have I said according to my own view, but partly according to the view of others, in order to enable young beginners to progress more easily",
      "label": "claim"
    },
